[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Maven dependencies**\n\nI need to determine if the Maven dependencies in the generated scaffold should include only compile/runtime transitives while excluding test-scoped modules. For meaningful coverage, I could consider calling copyResources/template without modules. The library is a site renderer, so it's important to include rendering documentation, which requires parser modules as extra dependencies. The user wants me to decide on setup beyond the standard generated scaffold, as extra Maven dependencies are permissible. Testing setup might require Sisu/Plexus injections to ensure everything interacts correctly.\n\n**Investigating dependencies**\n\nI'm trying to figure out if org.eclipse.sisu.plexus is an extra dependency since it has transitive runtime for javax.inject. Plexus-testing is only test-scoped and not transitive, which complicates things. I wonder if I can use org.eclipse.sisu.plexus in the classpath to manually instantiate components. It looks like I need to check the standard documentation for clarity. Should I also search online? Using curl could be a good idea to gather more info.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07abf6b04d3a2936016a3f594d63008193ad01a7c486d71b43\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1lV49uMGhNSVZTnsAp6OXHuKdt3ncvBHCeXx379UPHp0XYQUEQcN5SHNqJgwZmLhjuHaXFQ8g_1r0u00OwCiuxUQlv51tFpSToZJfqnKjAuiyF1tOSUZPpzAKnBHGZr8oRmuw6EmNpKUAR19q93svljqgFFcm75qvPsOIG6j9P3vFgaoeNbQXDY8-aNBv57KIf97BPKgpv-JZ_WDFgSkaPLkjzdzVIitpfKLrpinre-ArqEy54sQP3QbBYZnpc-QpzGS55YXcP_H9_RI3wGw0UdvHDl_-sWeWZsQJZMZglJHtw1vBCZHZReD0YMyFcJv4wmzJkWGOD10bsdJ89JbOf3rqfV2DTjv2j1h5cWvzYxSrH--m1PydIY4jKArTK7ojWEmF_Gxt12cTrebMr48wrDxdJ7v2au761rd5ugJM-CCQEyZUAojzwupWPbs0ix-y-8yScRekp6utJ10ugQn3VVv_ZBOvayMQg1cK2uSxiG8ciXZteFczsyOGSpH0u_sTrKwAxuBBLLBLZPLc652oe9sITvBByr5tR5jKmRngODTEw3OJ2_bdsOKe9EtEpy0PwdNYqSMJLFqfoYWT_jb31b7