 reachability metadata test effectively exercises the library. Using Plexus DI is standard for Maven components, but it might require metadata for Sisu or Guice, especially since doxia-site-renderer relies on Sisu/Plexus. Without plexus-testing, I could manually instantiate DefaultPlexusContainer from the transitive org.eclipse.sisu.plexus. Should I worry about the transitive dependency for PlexusContainer? For Native Image tests, the test app generally runs JUnit code, but adding plexus-testing might complicate things with Guice reachability.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 is a Maven/Plexus component whose meaningful rendering paths rely on injected components and Doxia parser modules that are not all present in the normal generated scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-testing:1.4.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Upstream 2.0.0 renderer tests use @PlexusTest and PlexusContainer.lookup(SiteRenderer.class); DefaultSiteRenderer has private injected fields for Velocity, Doxia, ParserModuleManager, and PlexusContainer, so direct construction is not enough for rendering coverage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact declares maven-artifact as provided, but the public skin API uses Artifact/DefaultArtifact; standalone tests need it to exercise createContextForSkin and skin-related rendering behavior.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0.0 POM notes Doxia modules are no longer in doxia-core and must be declared so component descriptors are discovered; upstream rendering tests add the APT module in test scope.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The renderer normally locates and renders Doxia source formats through parser module descriptors; xdoc is an upstream test-scope parser module for site rendering coverage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The renderer normally locates and renders Doxia source formats through parser module descriptors; fml is an upstream test-scope parser module for site rendering coverage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use the 2.0 API: DocumentRenderingContext replaces the old RenderingContext class, SkinResourceLoader is no longer public, DefaultSiteRenderer no longer has Plexus enableLogging, and SiteRenderingContext no longer has setUsingDefaultTemplate. Prefer obtaining SiteRenderer from a Plexus test container and render a small temporary site with a minimal skin/template and simple APT/XDoc/FML inputs rather than directly new-ing DefaultSiteRenderer for rendering paths.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.9.1 tests fail because they target removed/renamed APIs, not because a Docker image or environment variable is missing.\",\n    \"If the generated tests avoid full document rendering and only cover context/resource helpers, some added parser-module dependencies may remain unused; local Gradle and Native Image verification should decide final scope.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07abf6b04d3a2936016a3f59a2190081938ff12992f079a349\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 419, "output": 1711, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31826, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782536591108, "responseId": "resp_07abf6b04d3a2936016a3f598f93348193bba6b40861bf028e"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test risks**\n\nI need to think about risks: versions must align, like 2.0.0 or the mavenVersion. Extra Doxia modules can broaden classpath but might lead to unused dependencies if tests focus solely on merging documents. Integrating Plexus testing with native images could be tricky since it compiles everything, including all test dependencies. If I add plexus-testing and guice, will it complicate things further? It's important to ensure that reachability metadata tests don't interfere with the framework used in native tests.\n\n**Considering metadata testing**\n\nI need to ensure the reachability metadata test effectively exercises the library. Using Plexus DI is standard for Maven components, but it might require metadata for Sisu or Guice, especially since doxia-site-renderer relies on Sisu/Plexus. Without plexus-testing, I could manually instantiate DefaultPlexusContainer from the transitive org.eclipse.sisu.plexus. Should I worry about the transitive dependency for PlexusContainer? For Native Image tests, the test app generally runs JUnit code, but adding plexus-testing might complicate things with Guice reachability.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07abf6b04d3a2936016a3f599093c48193a41470746bca7083\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1miFA_dI5H9b45rMSNyM7uyeGks2oWWqNH0ZvfdB6_DMxhR_nHvgROFrqAaYZ00zGSPwWIEWoCeuRj9BkChJZRqXiIQbFFmrtgvVaf_W1kx9sexE2BrArfcXjVgHqNplhlCLIBI0svuk_jytHpJW6-_UW7gRVerpUzek_WvMsFZqxkzvg5hR5PqbrhAuWJCacpyfAOubCosegLK-nhW641vRyZ6OrsVVObgc8VeK5s1Xfos9kuEhllrKtjbXjs-EyQkH2ZXqrcmDAXy7hA0dbEWdq1yd87BoIrikIcX5hpXup1m_4Ph1U7di15b3Q63n0jaQaYLsyW-ad7bBYPIc0hjo9xF6H5C1zz051OQL2-c81tVhweEfTEfWqMHETYgQrvZYItry-jDc5fOgu-4vXtxvzn4Jn4hzFqVPJUy0kWLb07xiBBZr7WvcB_av58wIkCjXHKfjdRB5YFqzBbCd4bF3kV_MH8L7QSprlOjYXKizitTMmObyCPSGXva1bUm7sOKOCmh2mgTvQFnELnwzkA1CjMQ5aKGukzV0BD6JB7zMNDpe5RlTWbWeb7IoZDeTVQ